               poor man <supplied reason="lost">from the dung-heap? and places him</supplied> among kings [ . . . </p>
         </div>
            </div>
         
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>The phrasing in lines is from the Septuagint, Psalm 112.7-8:ὁ ἐγείρων ἀπὸ γῆς πτωχὸν καὶ ἀπὸ κοπρίας ἀνυψῶν πένητα (8) τοῦ καθίσαι αὐτὸν μετὰ ἀρχόντων; 
               the reading here is that suggested by Tod, to the editors of SEG 17. For its use in Christian inscriptions
               cf. <title>IGLS</title> IV. 1455, 1460, 1461 (<title>PHI</title> <ref target="https://epigraphy.packhum.org/text/243701">243701</ref>, 
               <ref target="https://epigraphy.packhum.org/text/243706">243706</ref>, <ref target="https://epigraphy.packhum.org/text/243707">243707</ref>), where, however, 
               the action is ascribed to the Lord, not to the Theotokos, as here.</p>
         </div>
         
